    <string name="intro_1_title">Pair your Bluetooth headset</string>
    <string name="intro_1_body">Before you start: pair your motorcycle headset or in-ears with each phone in the Android Bluetooth settings. Otherwise audio will run through the phone speaker and microphone.</string>
    <string name="intro_2_title">Tap "Search" on both phones</string>
    <string name="intro_2_body">On both phones, tap the big "Find a peer" button and allow visibility. When the other phone appears in the list, tap it and confirm "Yes" — the connection is up.</string>
    <string name="intro_3_title">Check the volume</string>
    <string name="intro_3_body">Once connected, the level bars (You / Peer) show that audio actually reaches the headset. Use your phone\'s hardware volume buttons to adjust.</string>

