    <!-- Help / FAQ -->
    <string name="menu_help">Help &amp; FAQ</string>
    <string name="help_title">Help &amp; FAQ</string>
    <string name="help_intro">Common issues we have hit during real-world testing and how to solve them.</string>

    <string name="help_t1_title">My Bluetooth headset is silent</string>
    <string name="help_t1_body">Make sure the headset is paired in the Android Bluetooth settings of each phone. SpeakEasy only routes audio through the headset once a real intercom connection is up — pairing alone is not enough. If you still hear nothing, try disconnecting and reconnecting the headset in the system settings.</string>

    <string name="help_t2_title">The connection drops every few minutes</string>
    <string name="help_t2_body">Most of the time this is the system battery optimization closing our background service. In Settings → System → "Disable battery optimization" make sure SpeakEasy is excluded. Also keep auto-reconnect (1/3/8 s) enabled — the app will rebuild the link automatically.</string>

    <string name="help_t3_title">My voice is too quiet or too loud</string>
    <string name="help_t3_body">Turn on "Automatic gain control" in Settings → Audio — it levels out loud and quiet voices in real time. To make individual peers louder or softer, use the "Peer volume" slider on the main screen during a connection.</string>

    <string name="help_t4_title">Wind noise drowns out the voice</string>
    <string name="help_t4_body">Switch the microphone mode to "Wind filter" or "Voice gate" on the main screen. Wind filter cuts low frequencies (the rumbling part of wind), voice gate sends nothing while you are silent — the peer hears no static during pauses.</string>

    <string name="help_t5_title">Latency is too high (more than 1 second)</string>
    <string name="help_t5_body">Bluetooth Classic shares radio time between SCO audio and RFCOMM data; spikes to 500–800 ms are normal. Beyond that the app automatically lowers the Opus bitrate (adaptive bitrate). If latency stays high, the stale-link detector forces a clean reconnect after about 12 seconds.</string>

    <string name="help_t6_title">Both phones must run the same version</string>
    <string name="help_t6_body">Audio frame format depends on the codec choice. Opus, μ-law and PCM are not compatible with each other — both phones must use the same codec. Default is Opus 24 kbps; only change it if the peer has the same setting.</string>
